yeah I agree Entrypoint is pain but safe bet when we want what user want to execute with a container. Having said that I was thinking more like set of instructions  a non-docker format being interpreted by buildah.  more like a simple shell script file  and we do `buildah <(cat myscript.sh)`.  

My intent was to reduce the Dockefile'sh syntax and make user feel more like writing shell script for building their containers. Not sure buildah DSL is the right word to explain ;)

@TomSweeneyRedHat  - an example of script like https://github.com/redhat-developer-demos/quarkus-java-builder/blob/master/bin/buildah.sh
